1 Sec. 33. Chapter 444 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. In addition to any other requirement set forth in title 58
4 relating to the disposal of a distributed generation system, an
5 owner of a distributed generation system that is being leased to a
6 customer or from which a customer purchases the output, shall
7 file with the Division of Environmental Protection of the State
8 Department of Conservation and Natural Resources a written plan
9 for the disposal of the distributed generation system at the end of
10 the useful life of the distributed generation system. The plan must:
11 (a) In lieu of disposal, provide for the reuse, refurbishment or
12 recycling of any solar photovoltaic panels; and
13 (b) Include, without limitation:
14 (1) The name of the person that will be responsible for the
15 disposal of the distributed generation system;
16 (2) The extent and methods by which the distributed
17 generation system will be recycled, refurbished or reused; and
18 (3) For any solar photovoltaic panels that will be recycled,
19 the percentage rate of the material recovery in weight.
20 2. Except as otherwise provided in this subsection, the
21 percentage rate of the material recovery in weight for any solar
22 photovoltaic panels that will be recycled at the end of the useful
23 life of a distributed generation system must not be less than 90
24 percent. The State Environmental Commission may, by
25 regulations adopted pursuant to subsection 3, prescribe alternative
26 methods to measure the recycled content of a solar photovoltaic
27 panel that will be recycled.
28 3. The State Environmental Commission shall adopt
29 regulations to carry out the requirements of this section.
30 4. As used in this section:
31 (a) “Distributed generation system” means a system or facility
32 directly installed on or at a residence that uses solar energy to
33 generate electricity.
34 (b) “Residence” means any dwelling in which title to the
35 individual unit is transferred to the owners.
